  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quality Assurance Technician",
  "description": "<h3>Key Responsibilties</h3>\n<p><strong>1. Product Qualification &amp; Validation</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Plan, execute, and monitor product qualification tests in accordance with internal procedures, customer requirements, and industry standards.</li>\n  <li>Set up and operate test equipment, measurement tools, and fixtures for qualification trials.</li>\n  <li>Verify dimensional, functional, and performance characteristics against specifications.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>2. Trial Management</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Support production trials and process validation runs.</li>\n  <li>Monitor trial progress, collect process/product data, and identify deviations or defects.</li>\n  <li>Work with engineering and production to resolve issues identified during trials.</li>\n  <li>Ensure trial samples are properly identified, stored, and traceable.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>3. Documentation &amp; Reporting</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare detailed qualification and trial reports, including test results, data analysis, and observations.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate records for compliance, traceability, and audit readiness.</li>\n  <li>Support creation or revision of quality-related documentation, including inspection plans, checklists, and SOPs.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>4. Continuous Improvement</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Participate in root cause analysis and corrective/preventive action activities related to trial failures.</li>\n  <li>Recommend process or inspection improvements based on trial results..</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Preferred Skills</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prefererably able to speak, write and understand simple English</li>\n  <li>Basic computer knowledge such as EXCEL</li>\n  <li>Basic knowledge on the use of measuring instruments e.g. Caliper, Dial gauge.</li>\n  <li>Must be able to carry 15kg of batteries</li>\n  <li>Must not be colour blind</li>\n</ul>",
